<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Elayne Trakand on 02-06-2002 12:31 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Most don't take invites unless they are applying for the guild.  Some will though, but it usually means you're not allowed to roll on any loot that drops.

Reasons are cause most have a merit system in place already and obviously guild members have more merit then non-guild invites.  Also large guilds don't progress to become large if they are equipping other people outside the guild.

If your just wanting the experience of doing a higher end raid then I'd talk to Asatru, The Guardian Lords or Utopian perhaps.  They aren't Uber guilds but most likely raiding higher level stuff then your guild.  Not sure on their policies though.

As for Rage, it used to be who was in the lair first got it first and there was usually always two or three waiting in line.  Leave the lair loose the camp, but there were always those that didn't like waiting in lines.  Since the change though best bet is to just go there and start camping it, talk with those that are currently or recently done Rage.

Hope this helps

Elayne Trakand
High Priest
Blades of Law
